programme.sub-title: One Unicorny Day!/ The Happy Horse Helpers!

programme.title: Mickey Mouse Mixed-Up Adventures
programme.sub-title: A Gollywood Wedding!/ No Dilly Dally in New Delhi!
programme.desc: Mickey and his pals travel to New Delhi, India, for the wedding of their friends Savi and Raj. The Happy Helpers assist an old friend who runs an auto-rickshaw business by being Tuk-Tuk Drivers for the day.

programme.title: Puppy Dog Pals
programme.sub-title: Chin Up, Pups / The Wind Beneath My Paws
programme.desc: The Pugs make a hospitalized child's wish come true; The Pugs search for Bob's Gift.

programme.title: Puppy Dog Pals
programme.sub-title: A Light for the Lighthouse / Music City Mishap
programme.desc: When the pugs find out that the light on Bob's favourite lighthouse isn't working, they go on a mission to fix it. Then, While in Nashville, Bingo and Rolly find a lost guitar and go on a mission to return it to its rightful owner.Guests: Darius Rucker, Jennifer Nettles..

programme.title: Puppy Dog Pals
programme.sub-title: Birthday Heros for Hero / Maple Cheer-Up
programme.desc: The pups must fix Hero's new birthday toy after Rolly and Keia accidentally break it. The Pugs head to Canada to save Bob's pancake surprise for Bonnie!

programme.title: T.O.T.S.
programme.desc: Freddy must face his fear of the dark when he and Pip are assigned a nighttime delivery. Pip hopes to speed through the next delivery, but they are tasked to deliver a baby sloth.

programme.title: T.O.T.S.
programme.sub-title: Hiccup Hazard/ The Great Robot Race

programme.title: Car SOS S5E5
programme.desc: Tim and Fuzz have taken on a legendary 1980s French hot hatch, the mighty Renault 5 GT Turbo. The car's owner, Ben, was part way through a full restoration when he was struck down with serious organ failure meaning his beloved GT ended up an unfinished project. Can Tim and Fuzz get his dream car back on the road?

programme.title: China Relics Decoded E6
programme.desc: Historian Sam Willis embarks on a journey through China to uncover how an ancient people crafted their world. From bronzes to jade, silk to porcelain, for eons the Chinese used their natural resources to hone their technology and culture. Discover the pivotal role China's crafts played in the development of a unique identity that influenced the course of world history.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E11
programme.desc: The Outer Banks Bluefin quota is filling up fast and with the legal limit for catching them at one fish a day, the competition is getting fierce. Northern and Southern fleets are determined to do whatever it takes to get paydays for their crews but when one captain loses his mate, a dangerous game ensues. Only the strong survive but who has what it takes in the battle between man and nature?

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E2
programme.desc: The Jungles of southern Yunnan are unique in China. Home to its greatest diversity of life. From primates to bears, fishing bats to bees and elephants to caterpillars, this is their story. With abundant resources life here should be easy but to survive, each must find its way to thrive. The creatures here have done exactly that through amazing adaptations some of which are filmed for the very first time.

programme.title: Inside Incredible Machines E6
programme.desc: For forty years, Nimitz class aircraft carriers have delivered US military might wherever it is needed, anywhere on the globe. But now, this legendary design is being phased out and new carriers are planned. But until they're ready, the giant Nimitz ships have to be kept at the forefront of military technology. In this episode, engineer and host Chad Zdenek spends a week on board the USS Carl Vinson to work with the highly trained specialist engineers, mechanics and sailors who keep this incredible floating city in perfect working order during a critical mission in the Pacific - training twenty F18 pilots who have never taken off from an Aircraft Carrier before. This gives Chad the chance to discover the five engineering innovations at the heart of America's most incredible Aircraft Carrier.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E13
programme.desc: Jordan checks out the bay area's biggest city, Oakland, California, long known for its tremendous diversity and thriving arts and entertainment scene, and amazing Asian cuisine. His first stop is Seawolf Public House in Jack London Square, a new local where Chef Jason Moniz mashes up classic pub food with international flavours.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E1
programme.desc: Jordan checks out Toronto, Canada's most diverse city, it dishes out all kinds of delights. He kicks off his tour at Chanticler, a French style bistro located in Parkdale, an artsy enclave with a hopping late vibe.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna S7E3
programme.desc: At the start of week three of the bluefin tuna season, every boat in the fleet has caught fish except for Hard Merchandise. Desperate to provide for his family, the pressure weighs heavily on Marciano's shoulders to land his first tuna and bring home a paycheck. Meanwhile, as Pinwheel fights to maintain the lead, second place Hot Tuna's Captain TJ Ott counts on his 10-year-old nephew, Danny, to bring luck to Hot Tuna and push them to the top.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S17E8
programme.desc: On its final approach to Zurich, Alitalia Flight 404 plows into a forested hillside killing everyone on board. Checking the DC-9's radar track, Swiss investigators immediately notice the aircraft was flying too low. But closer analysis of the evidence only deepens the mystery. Did a hidden flaw in the navigation system lead two pilots down a deadly path?

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S14E3
programme.desc: On October 4, 1992, El Al Flight 1862 Boeing 747-258F cargo jet with a heavy load of cargo loses control just minutes from the airport, rolling hard to the right and flying into an 11-storey apartment complex despite the pilots managing to turn the crippled aircraft around. Investigators discover a potentially lethal problem with every 747 in the sky.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S4E2
programme.desc: With a smoke-filled cabin and malfunctioned engines, will British Airways Flight 9 get to land in Perth, Australia on the fateful day of 24 June 1982?

programme.title: One Strange Rock E2
programme.desc: Ever wondered how our planet got here? It was born in a cosmic storm and shaped by violence. We're only here because of random collisions in a dangerous cosmos. It could have destroyed us, but instead constructed a planet from the rubble of the early solar system, gave us oceans in a bombardment from the heavens, and brought order to our world when two planets collided.

programme.title: Living Free With Kimi Werner E1
programme.desc: Champion spear fisher Kimi Werner visits a woman living a largely subsistence way of life and learns about her lifestyle. She's in pursuit of a deep truth about what it means to live more simply, more freely, and with a closer connection to nature.

programme.title: Inside The Ring
programme.desc: Inside the Ring is the extraordinary tale of how racers' quest for speed gave rise to a world famous grand prix circuit, the Nurburgring, and how it found new life as the ultimate automotive testing venue. With unprecedented access, we uncover what happens behind the latest top-secret facilities, and follow the development behind N division's new cutting-edge high-performance machine.

programme.title: Miracle Hospital S2E1
programme.desc: Merrily and her unborn baby could die if doctors can't navigate round a massive fibroid in her womb without causing catastrophic bleeding. University student Sam's rare tumours are causing life-threatening pressure in his brain. Using critical technology two surgeons conduct a marathon 8-hour operation to remove the largest tumour. Helen's spinal surgery requires millimeter precision if doctors are to cure her excruciating neck pain.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna S9E1
programme.desc: As the season opens, Gloucester's elite get challenged by top new fishermen. Captain Bob Cook and his crew on Fat Tuna vow to dethrone reigning champion Dave Carraro on FV-Tuna.Com. Tyler on Pinwheel faces off with Krakens captain Sam Law who is out to settle a personal score, while Hot Tuna is the target of Wasabi co-captains Zack Plante and Charlie Boivin who believe they've got more grit than TJ Ott. The new contenders arrival tests the Gloucester fleet in ways they've never faced before as a heated battle for bluefin begins on the Atlantic Ocean.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S17E10
programme.desc: En route to Boise, Idaho, Continental Airlines Flight 1713 is delayed on the tarmac in Denver where controllers struggle to keep departures on schedule amid heavy snow. When the plane is finally cleared for take-off, the DC-9 barely lifts off the ground before its banks sharply and crashes. Investigators find nothing wrong with the aircraft itself, but what they eventually uncover changes commercial flight forever.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E12
programme.desc: Every second on the water is valuable with the Outer Banks Bluefin Season nearing an end. This year, strict limits on fishing mean boats can only bring in one fish a day and while the luckiest Northern and Southern captains battle it out for the title of top-earner, every other boat scrambles to salvage their season, snagging any Bluefin they can before it's too late.

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E3
programme.desc: China's bamboo forest is full of secrets and surprises, including the legendary giant panda, red panda and Tibetan macaque, and a host of other unusual creatures such as the jewelled flower mantis, bamboo bats and moustached toads that have found ingenious ways to survive in this kingdom of giant grass.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E3
programme.desc: The Ferrari factory is building the new FF, the first four-wheel drive Ferrari with four full-sized seats. The FF's 12-cylinder engine is one of the most powerful engines ever built at the factory in Maranello, at 651 Horsepower. The engine block is actually cast there and must go through multiple quality checks before it's ready to join the final assembly line.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S2E2
programme.desc: It's one thing to have a mega kitchen that feeds thousands, but a traveling mega kitchen that feeds thousands is quite another. Watch how ISKCON's Yatra Kitchen travels across India, setting up almost overnight to feed Krishna-devotees from all over the world.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna S7E4
programme.desc: It's tournament time in Gloucester and when inexperienced fishermen - or googans as the commercial fleet refer to them - crowd the water, the fleet has to fight through additional aggravating obstacles standing in their way of earning a paycheck. While googans wreak havoc with their carelessness, some commercial boats will manage to land fish against the odds while others will go home empty-handed. And one boat will score the biggest payday so far this season, but not without a fight.

programme.title: Lost Treasures of Egypt E1
programme.desc: In this episode, archaeologists unlock the mysteries of Egypt's most famous pharaoh, Tutankhamun. We unearth a long lost box of treasures from inside Tutankhamun's tomb. New technology reveals why this boy kings resting place remained hidden from tomb robbers for thousands of years and we join the team who are tasked with transporting Tutankhamun's priceless treasures, on a one in a lifetime journey through the desert. Whilst a team of archaeologists make a new discovery of a lifetime when they open a 4000-year-old tomb.

programme.title: Lost Treasures of Egypt E2
programme.desc: Archaeologists investigate one of the greatest female pharaohs in history - Hatshepsut. A team digging around her iconic temple find clues about her powerful reign. A rare discovery inside one of Hatshepsut's ancient quarries sparks an investigation which leads to the magnificent temple of Karnak.. And one archaeologist discovers dramatic evidence about the lives of women in ancient Egypt whilst excavating mummy parts from inside an ancient tomb.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E14
programme.desc: Drain the Oceans unlocks the secrets of how the Japanese Empire rose to power in the Pacific and how it harnessed superior technology turning that devastating firepower against the Allies. It reveals hidden secrets of a catastrophic attack on Australia that gave Japan control of the region and how its extraordinary tactics brought the British Empire to its knees.

programme.title: One Strange Rock E3
programme.desc: Earth protects itself from the sun. The David and Goliath story of Earths relationship with its greatest threat, our seemingly benign Sun. The Sun is the big violent boss of the Solar System throwing out devastating particles and deadly radiation. Without several shields, one generated by our unique planetary core, another by our atmosphere, and a third by our interconnected weather systems, life on Earth would never have survived.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S2E4
programme.desc: It is story of journey, travelled by tribal children from interiors of Odisha to a national level and the world stage. It is a world's largest tribal school. This is also an inspiring & uplifting human story about empowering the poorest of the poor. Feeding their dreams with education and a full plate...is the Kalinga institute of social sciences. Presenting the MEGA facts of the kitchen, 25,000 children are fed 3 meals a day (approx. 76000 in total) in a 10,000-capacity dining hall on an 80 acre campus.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E10
programme.desc: Now with fossil fuels becoming increasingly sparse, one company is trying to change the way we commute; this is the story behind the world's first fully electric premium sedan – the Tesla Model S. Tesla's electrical experts in Fremont, CA are gearing up for mass production in a groundbreaking new Mega Factory – but will the Model S take the world by storm?

programme.title: No Man Left Behind E1
programme.desc: During the Battle of Mogadishu, a squad of US Rangers and Delta Force including Keni Thomas and Randy Ramaglia, rope down from Black Hawk helicopter for a mission to capture two top lieutenants of rebel leader Mohamed Aidid but their Hawk gets shot down by outgunned ground troops. Another Black Hawk flies in to help but is hit and downed, putting pilot Mike Durant in captive for 11 days.

programme.title: The Story Of God With Morgan Freeman S3E4
programme.desc: Sin is a part of the human condition. But can we conquer it? Morgan Freeman travels the world, from California to Italy to Vietnam, to understand how different faiths think of and deal with sin. He'll learn about the bloody Medieval practice of self-flagellation, the mysterious Sin Eaters, and the Confucian view of sin. He'll also meet a man who is trying to atone for his years as an executioner.

programme.title: Underworld, Inc. S2E4
programme.desc: We follow the dirty drug dollars from American trap houses to wholesalers and transporters, funneling billions into Mexico's money laundering cycle. US authorities are closing in on cartel cash. If drug lords want their narco cheddar cleaned and moved into the banking system, they have to get it to Mexico.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E13
programme.desc: There's only forty-eight hours left in the Outer Banks Bluefin season, and while a Southern boat leads the fleet, one Northern vessel continues their assault for the top earning spot. With final paychecks on the line, big fish on the hook and so little time, a fight to the finish is the only guarantee.

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E4
programme.desc: China's vast grasslands are a hard place to survive. Battered by ferocious and unpredictable storms throughout the year, the inhabitants of these grasslands have to be adaptable and tenacious to survive. During the short three-month window of summer, the plains residents have to race against time to raise their young before the onset of autumn and winter begin.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures: America's War E6
programme.desc: Spring 1944. An allied invasion of Hitler's Fortress Europe is inevitable, and under the leadership of distinguished commander Field Marshall Erwin Rommel, the Germans begin a comprehensive programme to turn coastal areas into killing zones. But they still have no idea where and when the invasion will come, and in a fascinating game of cat and mouse, the Allies keep them guessing all the way up to 6th June 1944 - D-Day.

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E6
programme.desc: In this final episode of Gok's Chinese Takeaway, Gok Wan returns home to London to discover Westernized version of Cantonese cuisine like Chop Suey, Crispy Duck and Sweet and Sour Pork. Finally, Gok draws on the food and culinary influences from his travels throughout Europe, Asia and Australia in order to create his ultimate celebratory feast of Chinese food from around the world.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna S7E5
programme.desc: It's week seven of fishing and boats are teaming up to share information, in a bid to catch more fish. But when Paul Hebert, captain of the fleet's current top-earning boat, Wicked Pissah, takes pity on Captain TJ Ott of Hot Tuna, who have struggled to catch for more than a week, Paul's decision to help them just might backfire on him.

programme.title: Science of Stupid S7E5
programme.desc: In this episode we learn the science behind the fails, when riding a horse through water, steering a radio-controlled plane and underestimating the power of ocean tides.

programme.title: Science of Stupid S7E5
programme.desc: In this episode we learn the science behind the fails, when riding a horse through water, steering a radio-controlled plane and underestimating the power of ocean tides.

programme.title: Science of Stupid S7E5
programme.desc: In this episode we learn the science behind the fails, when riding a horse through water, steering a radio-controlled plane and underestimating the power of ocean tides.

programme.title: Street Genius S1E3
programme.desc: Tim Shaw’s scientific experiments take in everything from Hollywood-style car chases to bottle caps and bicycle wheels, as he exposes how the world works. Big bangs are on the agenda as Tim attempts to blow up his pickup truck. For the finale, he will attempt to keep his car off the ground using the power of household vacuum cleaners.

programme.title: Street Genius S1E4
programme.desc: Tim Shaw, our guide the to the sensational world of science, creates lightning, passes a live wire through a pickle, blasts through ice blocks, and attempts to create instant fried turkey from frozen. Along the way the people he meets and the viewers are invited to guess the outcome of his incredible experiments.

programme.title: One Strange Rock E4
programme.desc: Our rock is special - it's alive. Though the building blocks of life are common across the universe, life is rare. So what is it about planet earth that sets it apart? What dynamic forces, what coincidences took a bunch of dead ingredients and transformed them into something as insanely intricate as Life? And if happened here could it happen elsewhere?

programme.title: Nick Baker's Eco Malaysia
programme.desc: British naturalist, Nick Baker, travels to South East Asia to embark on a unique eco-adventure in the Malaysian Peninsula - one of the most bio-diverse landscapes on the planet. His journey begins in the 130 million-year-old Belum-Temengor rainforest, and then he travels to the lush valley of Lenggong to explore the caves of Gua Gunung Runtuh before trying his hand at elephant caretaking.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures S4E2
programme.desc: From Monte Cassino to San Pietro and ultimately the defence of Rome, this is the amazing story of one of the toughest defensive structures that the Nazis ever conceived. The Allies thought an advance from the south would be a quick way to bring down the Nazis, but they were wrong. Hitler, determined to defend every inch of ground, ordered a series of defensive lines stretching across the entire Italian peninsula, stalling the Allies' advance into the Third Reich for almost two years.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E15
programme.desc: Drain the Oceans unlocks the secrets of how the Roman Empire controlled the seas of the Ancient world and how it harnessed the power of volcanoes to defy nature itself. It reveals the extraordinary secrets of one of the oldest shipwrecks in the world, and unearths a port lost for centuries under Italian soil.

programme.title: Lawless Island Alaska Compilations S2E5
programme.desc: One time city girl, Mary's story breaks the mold. Living alone in Alaska is tough and the learning curve is steep. Luckily, she has the help of the Lawless Island community to help her stand on her own two feet.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S8E7
programme.desc: A failed businessman, plumber Paul Keanys desperately looks for opportunities to make ends meet for his family. Acquainted with a local drug dealer, Paul agrees to smuggle six kilos of cocaine from Venezuela back to Dublin. But when he is stopped at the airport in Caracas, Paul unfortunately lives to regret his decision.

programme.title: United Plates Of America E6
programme.desc: Los Angeles is not only the center of the world's biggest film and television industry, it is also the leader in setting trends. For many years now LA has been on a health kick, making it relatively easy for people to live a healthier lifestyle. In this episode, we're taking a closer look at this healthy culture and seeing what the Hollywood life tastes like.

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E1
programme.desc: Gok travels around Barcelona and seeks Western Mediterranean cuisine in this episode. He attempts to make Barcelona sausages with the help of a professional artisan sausage maker. Also, Gok looks for the renowned Chinese restaurant in the territory where peking duck and dim sum are served distinctively in Spanish-style with its original appearance.

programme.title: John Torode's Asia E3
programme.desc: As a lifelong lover of Chinese food, when John Torode's tour of Asian cuisine stops off in Beijing, he is understandably elated. Naturally John heads straight to a Beijing's most loved Peking Duck restaurant in the heart of the Hutongs and is fascinated to see and then taste a traditionally inflated and roasted Peking Duck.

programme.title: What's For Sale With A View S2E3
programme.desc: Wine enthusiasts Christina and Ed are ready to make their lifelong dream of having a view of a lush green vineyard come true. Their Italian and Chilean roots have led them on a quest to re-locate to wine country.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E5
programme.desc: Dairy, Drugs and Dogs headline in today's visit to Heathrow. On the airfield Airside Ian goes for promotion, whilst inside the terminals Queen of T2 Sue saves a musician from missing his concert and in security there's a serious breach.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E4
programme.desc: Flying into Heathrow: an endangered parrot, and a polar vortex! Whilst Officers Dave and Terry hunt for a wanted man gone missing on a plane, Airside Ian and stickler-for-the-rules Steve battles snow in a blizzard to keep the runways open.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S2E2
programme.desc: Jordan's first stop in Charlotte is in NoDa, the city's vibrant arts district. He's kicking off his night at Haberdish, a North Carolina style southern kitchen and wine bar. He's there to learn the secret behind their mouthwatering fried chicken, which some say is the best in the south. Jordan's next stop is Uptown but underground, as he heads to The Cellar at Duckworth's.

programme.title: A Taste Of South Africa E3
programme.desc: Matt meets many, many cows. He learns about, admires and milks South Africa's indigenous Nguni breed in Msinga, Kwa Zulu Natal. Matt meets Xoliswa Ndoyiya (Nelson Mandela's personal chef) to cook the late president's favourite sour milk recipe (umphokoqo) and share memories of her time cooking for an icon.

programme.title: Island Hunter E3
programme.desc: Easy island vibes, lots of amazing local rum, brilliant natural landscapes and those amazing beaches! Of course, Island Hunter is in Jamaica! But in this episode, host Liesel Hlista shows you a different side of the Irie nation; away from the hordes of people unleashed via cruise liners! She starts off with a quick glimpse and an impromptu jam session at the birthplace of Bob Marley, Trench town, noshes on the most delicious ice cream this side of the hemisphere, and plunges into Mystic mountain's waterfalls. Jamaica is known for being the home of the all-inclusive resort and Liesel finds out exactly why that is - with stays at Ian Fleming inspired Golden eye Hotel as well as Sunset at the Palms! Lazy tubing down the river, limestone foot massages, topped up with historic food tours and experiencing local cuisines such as jerk chicken and the amazing seafood; this is Jamaica, Island Hunter style!

programme.title: Route Awakening S3E4
programme.desc: Dr Jonathan Clements, historian, author and TV host, meets the little known Lisu ethnic minority and gets himself into Lisu courtship and wedding but also learns about manly activities like making crossbows, playing musical instruments and climbing a ladder of upturned knives.

programme.title: Around The World In 80 Dishes E5
programme.desc: Although Manu has visited Tokyo before, this time he is on his own and has a tight budget. Still, he is keen to learn and discover as much as he can. His first stop is the legendary fish market to learn about the renowned tuna sold there but he has to make it through the craziness of the Tokyo fish market first.

programme.title: United Plates Of America E6
programme.desc: Los Angeles is not only the center of the world's biggest film and television industry, it is also the leader in setting trends. For many years now LA has been on a health kick, making it relatively easy for people to live a healthier lifestyle. In this episode, we're taking a closer look at this healthy culture and seeing what the Hollywood life tastes like.

programme.desc: Kolkata is home to India's largest Chinese community, which has been in existence for over 200 years, leaving a huge impact on the local food scene. They are fiercely proud of their Hakka-style cuisine and David can't wait to get his fill. He spends the day with a family that produces and sells their own Chinese sauce, eating their delicious momos and fried chicken.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E11
programme.desc: David finally fulfills his dream of visiting the Golden Temple, the holiest Sikh gurudwara in the world. The langar inside the Golden Temple, where the community comes and cooks together, serves upwards of 100,000 people a day and David gets to experience the mania of the meal preparation firsthand. Later, David takes a local food tour to sample all of the local Punjabi delicacies.

programme.title: Confucius Was A Foodie S3E4
programme.desc: The taste of Chinese medicinal herbs, bitter flavor is said to clear 'heat', strengthen the stomach, and promote salivation. Bitterness in often found in Chinese cooking, but rarely used alone. Christine cooks a popular local bitter ingredient, and makes a less than delicious visit to a Traditional Chinese Medicine shop, experiencing firsthand the power of bitter herbs.

programme.title: Around The World In 80 Dishes E5
programme.desc: Although Manu has visited Tokyo before, this time he is on his own and has a tight budget. Still, he is keen to learn and discover as much as he can. His first stop is the legendary fish market to learn about the renowned tuna sold there but he has to make it through the craziness of the Tokyo fish market first.

programme.title: Ugly House To Lovely House With George Clarke S2E3
programme.desc: Martyn and Sally are desperate to transform their totally impractical 1980's upside down house. Dominated by a big double garage this mishmash of living spaces is so badly laid out that to get from the kitchen to the garden you have to go through the master bedroom. Not ideal for a family that love to barbeque. George teams them up with innovative architect Greg Blee. Greg has recently been busy designing lavish million pound projects in the Caribbean. Can he turn his talents to something much smaller, and will he be able to create a design that works on Martyn and Sally's budget of just £65,000?

programme.title: Mega Food E2
programme.desc: It's a 24-hour culinary operation akin to a military exercise. 250 chefs turn more than 100 tons of raw ingredients into a quarter of a million meals in just seven days. Even the loading process is an exhausting challenge. All of these happen on board the world's largest cruise ship, Royal Caribbean's Oasis of the Seas.

programme.title: Easyjet: Inside The Cockpit S1E2
programme.desc: Follow the rookie pilots as they take their first steps from the flight school classroom into the flight simulator, and on to flying large jets with hundreds of passengers on board. This episode, freshly-qualified 20-year-old Ryan Clyde lands for the first time in the dark in Paris with passengers on board - with the added complication that one of them has never flown before, and is extremely nervous. Meanwhile cadet Sophie Trunan learns how to deal with G-forces, and the firm's training captains jet off to France to showcase their skills to seven fledgling pilots.

programme.title: Island Hunter E5
programme.desc: Hong Kong is Asia's world city and this episode is a complete 360 from the melee of tropical island paradises. Hong Kong is famous for it's skyscraper strewn skyline and in this episode, local girl Lesley Chiang is on a mission to show a different side of Hong Kong. Her journey starts off in Hong Kong bay where she gets a taste of the 5 star life at the Ritz Carlton. Pampering at the 108th floor spa, dining at Michelin 2 star rated Ting Lung Heen, and beyond! Lesley checks out the art scene of Soho, and PMQ, an establishment geared towards Hong Kong's budding arts and crafts talent. At night time, local nightlife expert Johannes Pong shows Lesley the wild side of town as they bounce around the latest bars and clubs. When it's time to chow, Jowett Yu, a rising star in the culinary world shows Lesley his favorite hometown hang outs; roast geese to yummy sea food bites. Taking a break from Hong Kong island, Lesley also checks out the nearby Lantau island where she gets a taste o.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E12
programme.desc: David is in Amritsar - a city known for the warmth of its people and its amazing food - exploring all the different facets of Punjabi culture. He meets up with some locals, tries specialty Punjabi dishes and even learns to tie his own turban. He also spends time with two contrasting local families: one is vegetarian and the other loves their meat.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E2
programme.desc: Having explored the beef territory of northern Mexico, it’s time to head for some seafood as Peter Kuruvita descends 2000 metres by train to explore Mexico’s Pacific coast - home of prawns, giant oysters and the original fish tacos.

programme.title: Confucius Was A Foodie S3E5
programme.desc: Despite popular belief ‘spicy' in Chinese cuisines is not always hot! In various Chinese cuisines, spices are complex and varied. Chef Christine visits the Malaysian island of Penang, a location historically important to the story of spice trade with TV celebrity Chef Wan for a fun and fact filled visit to the Tropical Spice Garden.

programme.title: Around The World In 80 Dishes E6
programme.desc: Manu has just one country left before making his final journey back to London, and the finale of his worldwide odyssey. America offers up many amazing food experiences, with Mexican dishes and food trucks, pastrami sandwiches, ribs by a soul food legend, and mouthwatering Italian food. With 30 days and $20,000 to spend, will Manu realize his dream of making it around the world Phileus Fogg-style?

programme.title: Ugly House To Lovely House With George Clarke S2E4
programme.desc: Chris Dyson is undoubtedly one of Britain's most respected architects, used to generous budgets and renowned for high-impact transformations. George pairs him up with Wendy and Allan who are desperate to transform their horrible looking 60's property into something more modern. Adamant the house needs both a drastic makeover externally and a major reconfiguration internally, can Chris satisfy their high expectations whilst sticking to their modest £150K budget.

programme.title: Shark Men S3E8
programme.desc: The Shark Men divide and conquer to catch a shark, but the division leads to danger. While divers scout for hammerheads, Todd is off by himself and hooks a tiger shark. The support boats rush over to assist Todd while leaving the lead scientists alone in dangerous waters. Also, Costa Rica's Cocos Island is a designated protected area and rangers are keeping a skeptical eye on the Shark Men.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S4E4
programme.desc: Nature's vicious battles for survival come in every scale, from 6-ton elephants fighting in a testosterone-fueled blind fury, to slime-covered amphibian kick boxers dangling in the jaws of death. This is a no-holds barred look at cold-hearted killers in the wild, revealing ambush experts with piercing canines, slithering assassins with crushing coils, and multi-layered fangs dealing death.

programme.title: When Predators Attack (Mashups) E2
programme.desc: Crocodilians are super reptiles, ancient survivors from prehistoric times. Over 200 million years ago, they dominated all continents and oceans, posing a threat to even the mighty T-Rex. As the human population rises, and we encroach further on this ancient predator's turf, attacks increase. And we are no match for their prehistoric power.

programme.title: Killer Animal Tactics
programme.desc: From top predators to clever creatures, these killers are some of the most armed and dangerous animals in the world. In order to survive, they use some of the scariest strategies and lethal weapons like ambush, camouflage, claws and paws, venom, pack hunting and more to take down prey. The name of the game is kill or be killed!

programme.title: Alaska Animal Rescue E3
programme.desc: There's a baby boom in Alaska! The rescue team from the Alaska SeaLife Center hits the road when a newborn sea otter gets separated from its mom. If this baby is alright, she'll require round-the-clock care. A new baby also arrives at the Alaska Raptor Center when a bald eaglet falls from its nest. But there's no time to rest. The team must also jump into action to save a stranded, injured eagle that's lost a fight. And at the Alaska Wildlife Conservation Center, two foxes rescued as kits are getting a habitat upgrade. But first they have to learn all the necessary tricks to make the big move.

programme.title: Monster Fish S5E1
programme.desc: Biologist Zeb Hogan travels to Australia to try and track down two of the country's most dangerous river shark species - one thought to be the biggest, and the other possibly the rarest. First he tackles the mighty Bull Shark, a deadly predator capable of growing to the lengths of a small car. He then sets his sights on the Speartooth Shark, which has never had a confirmed sighting in the wild.

programme.title: Fish My City With Mike Iaconelli E2
programme.desc: Mike's in Taiwan to search for three species of fish. One fish is a drain dwelling monster that originally escaped from fish farms, another is a mysterious visitor from the open seas that makes fleeting visits to the city via a watery highway and the final challenge is a true monster, who's reputation includes biting its prey clean in half and having teeth like a shark.

programme.title: Wild 24 S1E2
programme.desc: This film follows animals over 24 hours living in and around one of the driest regions on Earth: the Atacama Desert in northern Chile. A group of survivors live here, between the rich Pacific Ocean and the foothills of the Andes. Weird rabbit-like rodents, a big cat, hump-less camelids, iconic dancing birds and even penguins battle against the odds in a land of extreme heat and cold.

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E2
programme.desc: This episode welcomes viewers to the deadly world of the most feudal families, almighty monarchs, territorial clans, and awesome armies of the animal kingdom. Capturing polar bears feasting like kings, giraffes in neck-jousting battles over females and deadly Hyena sibling infighting, it is all about winning the game of thrones of the savage land.

programme.title: India's Wild Edens
programme.desc: India: vibrant, breath-taking and extreme. A vast land of striking contrasts whose boundaries encompass scorching deserts, verdant forests and soaring, snow-dusted peaks. A realm where man lives cheek- by-jowl with the natural world; home to over a billion people and some of the most spectacular wildlife on the planet.

programme.title: Alaska Animal Rescue E4
programme.desc: It's midsummer and the state of Alaska is battling uncontrollable wildfires and record-breaking heat. An orphaned sea otter pup narrowly escapes the flames while the rest of the SeaLife Center combats heavy smoke and awaits the arrival of new a puffin hatchling. At the Wildlife Conservation Center, Howie prepares for a once-in-a-lifetime expedition to survey wild wood bison, but the heat is causing complications for their own breeding herd. And at the Alaska Raptor Center, wildfires up north present a problem for a very unique owl.

programme.title: Monster Fish S3E13
programme.desc: Dr. Zeb Hogan travels across Oceania in the remote South Pacific, tracking an elusive and almost mythical giant predator, the snake-like giant eels. There are 9 different species of Long Fin Eel throughout the Pacific, and Zeb aims to find two of the biggest, the New Zealand Longfin Eel and its cousin, the Mottled Eel.

programme.desc: In the final days of the Cocos Island expedition, the Shark Men are in a race against the clock. To tag the ever elusive hammerheads, the team resorts to midnight fishing and swimming with sharks. And at the moment when teamwork is needed, the team and equipment breaks down. The crane dies and Denny disappears. With only hours to go to implant the crucial tags, will the Shark Men pull through?

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S4E5
programme.desc: “Power Struggles' reveals how the most epic battles can be won or lost in a split second. In the world of wild animal fights, nothing is ever certain. We see a female leopard fight a bigger male for her lunch and her life, discover the complex competition amongst the world's largest great apes, and see how a Nile monitor lizard can turn its tail into a show-stopping weapon.

programme.title: When Predators Attack (Mashups) E3
programme.desc: Bears are iconic symbols of nature, a treasure to see in the wild?when kept at an appropriate distance. With habitat loss and a changing climate, the world's strongest bears are inching closer to our homes. And nothing beats their killer package. Watch what unfolds when black bears, grizzlies, and giant polar bears face off against prey and people, in a final attempt to stay alive.

programme.title: Cat Attack-Tics
programme.desc: There are 38 species of wild cats on Earth and they live and hunt in almost any terrain. Over millions of years, they have honed their strategy to attack a prey of a specific size. From tree-climbing leopards to skull-crushing Jaguars, from fast-swimming fishing cats to quick-digging sand cats - watch the killer strategies that make wild cats possibly the deadliest family on the planet.

programme.title: The Monster Project E3
programme.desc: Judah Friedlander is in Texas to investigate the myths and legends of one of the most fascinating and elusive beings, the Chupacabra. Its translated name is Goat Sucker, legend says that it drains the blood from its victims leaving behind puncture holes, and that it has the ability to change its colour. So far all sightings have turned out to be coyotes, but is there any truth behind the legend?

programme.title: Monster Fish S5E2
programme.desc: Zeb Hogan hunts for the fresh water Whipray in the Daily River, northern Australia. The largest one caught so far was 10 feet across and weighed around 800 pounds, with a barb over 12 inches long. He then heads to Thailand on the trail of a giant Stingray, reported to be 600 pounds. These rays are said to grow to the size of small trucks. If true, this would be the largest fresh water fish ever.

programme.title: Fish My City With Mike Iaconelli E3
programme.desc: Mike travels to London, England in search of three of the great city's most iconic fish species. One is a fearsome predator that will even devour birds, another is piscine royalty that is often known as 'The Prince of the River' and one is a sentimental favourite that has recovered from a devastating disease outbreak.

programme.title: Wild 24 S1E3
programme.desc: From the forests to the waters, this is a snapshot of the extraordinary lives of Tasmania's animals over 24 hours, including nocturnal Tasmanian Devils feeding on carrion and walking fishes trekking on the seabed. This land of unique creatures, situated in the south of the Australian mainland has an extraordinary variety of strange and bizarre creatures.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S4E3
programme.desc: Streetwise snake-catcher Simon Keys and his sassy herpetologist girlfriend, Siouxsie Gillett, rush around Snake City to save snakes that have ventured into human territory. They hunt down a frighteningly fast black mamba in a cluttered kitchen, and a Mozambique spitting cobra under a bath that's showering Simon with venom. All before he has to face his irrational fear of heights while trying to retrieve a green mamba from a tree.

programme.title: Jaguars Vs Crocs
programme.desc: Veteran wildlife photographer Steve Winter and cameraman Bertie Gregory capture the remarkable lives of Jaguars in the Pantanal of Brazil. A mother jaguar teaches her cub survival while a determined male jaguar named Scarface dives headfirst into the river to tackle the deadliest of opponents - 6-foot long caiman. Clever capybaras and playful giant otters stick with their family members to avoid being jaguar dinner.

programme.title: Savage Kingdom: Uprising E3
programme.desc: The Marsh Pride's ageing King, Sekekama, is forced to lead his family into hostile territory, in a mission to save them from a vicious drought gripping the Kingdom. His great gamble leads him into bloody contest against old rivals and new. But it is his control over one treacherous son that will determine Sekekama's hold on power - and the future of his own legacy.

programme.title: Monster Fish S3E12
programme.desc: Dr. Zeb Hogan travels to the wild and remote Kamchatka in Russia's Far East, home to a mass migration of millions of Salmon. This isolation has preserved one of the world's last wild salmon sanctuaries, and to explore this area, he seeks help from a team of world-class kayakers and tackles white water rapids, bears, volcanoes and poachers to find out why this land is home to so many Salmon.

programme.title: Wild Korea E1
programme.desc: Korea is known as a modern, high tech nation; but beyond the bustle of the cities there's a land of stunning natural beauty and remarkable wildlife. There are lush wetlands and mudflats in contrast to the soaring mountains and turbulent seas; and the beautiful goshawk, bottleneck dolphin and curious racoon dog thrive alongside Korea's traditional people as they have for many thousands of years.

programme.title: Fish My City With Mike Iaconelli E4
programme.desc: Doubling down, Mike challenges himself to catching six different species of fish; three exotic species that have all travelled a long way to make themselves at home in Miami's fresh-water canals, and three salt-water classics including the fastest and one of the oldest fish living today.

programme.title: Wild 24 S1E4
programme.desc: Antarctica is one of the most remote and pristine wildernesses on the planet. Night here can last for months and in the peak of summer the sun never sets. Despite of the inhabitability, life abounds in Antarctica. Megafauna such as humpback whales and orcas, massive seals and stately penguins all take the brutal conditions head on and thrive.

programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol S6E1
programme.desc: Winter, summer, spring or fall there's never a shortage of work to be done on the farm in central Michigan - and never a shortage of problems - especially when it comes to farm animals. programme.title: The Divine Fury
programme.desc: Setelah terbangun dengan luka misterius di tangannya, seorang petinju mendapati dirinya bertarung melawan kekuatan jahat yang menyebabkan malapetaka di bumi.

programme.title: Truck
programme.desc: Seorang sopir truk tak sengaja melihat pembunuhan oleh sebuah geng. Ia bersedia membantu membuang mayat-mayat itu agar tetap dibiarkan hidup. Namun, situasi memburuk ketika seorang pembunuh berantai menumpang truknya.

programme.title: RV: Resurrected Victims
programme.desc: Suatu hari, ibu jaksa Jin-hong yang sudah meninggal kembali ke rumah dan mencoba membunuhnya. Ia pun segera menjadi tersangka utama atas pembunuhan ibunya.

programme.title: Forbidden Dream
programme.desc: Dua penemu Korea menjalin hubungan selama 20 tahun sembari memajukan bidang astronomi.

programme.title: Luck-Key
programme.desc: Sebuah kasus pencurian identitas mendatangkan sederet peristiwa lucu ketika seorang aktor yang tengah mengalami kesulitan dan sesosok pembunuh bayaran bertukar kehidupan.

programme.title: Midnight Runners
programme.desc: Dua mahasiswa dari Universitas Kepolisian Nasional Korea memutuskan untuk bekerjasama dan menyelidiki sebuah insiden penculikan.

programme.title: The Witch: The Subversion
programme.desc: Ja-yoon melarikan diri dari pemerintah dan diadopsi oleh pasangan senior dan kehilangan semua ingatannya. Kemudian, ketika ia muncul di sebuah program TV, orang-orang asing mulai muncul dalam hidupnya.

programme.title: Tough As Iron
programme.desc: Berlatarkan suatu pelabuhan di selatan Busan, seorang pemuda berjuang untuk menemukan pekerjaan dan merawat ibunya yang menderita demensia. Ia lalu terlibat dengan sekelompok mafia demi membayar tagihan rumah sakit.

programme.title: Wide Awake
programme.desc: Seorang anak laki-laki yang mengalami trauma setelah menjalani pembiusan lokal saat operasi jantung terlibat dalam serangkaian pembunuhan 25 tahun kemudian.

programme.title: My Tutor Friend
programme.desc: Su-wan dipaksa untuk memberikan bimbingan belajar pada Ji-hoon, seorang siswa SMA berusia 21 tahun yang sangat nakal.

programme.title: My Boss, My Teacher
programme.desc: Doo-sik adalah seorang mahasiswa senior di pagi hari dan bekerja di sebuah geng di malam hari. Namun, masalah muncul saat bosnya meminta ia bekerja untuknya di pagi hari, saat ia berada di kampus.

programme.title: Heung-boo: The Revolutionist
programme.desc: Sebuah sandiwara jalanan menjadi populer pada masa Dinasti Joseon. Heung-boo, sang penulis naskah, banyak diincar oleh para elit politik yang ingin menggunakan ketenarannya untuk kepentingan mereka sendiri.

programme.title: Singles
programme.desc: Tiga sekawan yang menghadapi pasang surut kehidupan mencoba untuk tinggal bersama. Namun, persahabatan mereka diuji kala dua diantara mereka tidur bersama.

programme.title: Radio Dayz
programme.desc: Sekelompok tim nan unik bersatu untuk membuat siaran langsung drama radio pertama di Joseon saat masa penjajahan Jepang pada tahun 1933.

programme.title: Inside Men
programme.desc: Seorang mantan antek politik berusaha membalas dendam usai dijatuhkan oleh seorang politisi kejam di kala sesosok penyelidik yang gigih berusaha menemukan bukti adanya hubungan di antara keduanya.

programme.title: Gonjiam: Haunted Asylum

programme.title: Lost And Found
programme.desc: Ji-ho diam-diam jatuh cinta pada pria yang sama selama 10 tahun terakhir. Saat ia tertabrak mobil sang pria, ia berbohong demi menjadi dekat dengannya, namun justru berakhir dengan bencana.

programme.title: Along With Gods: Last 49 Days
